\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Emily Negroni\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4503:\"\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-normal-font-size\">Maintenance Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">The latest update of The Events Calendar focuses on accessibility enhancements and ensuring that organizer info displays correctly on the single event page. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\">testing updates</a> on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-fixes\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixes</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p>Bugs squashed in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Evaluate correctly whether the email and phone field of a non-password protected organizer should display and by default the organizer&#8217;s website opens in a new tab</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column2553086_b06682-e3\"><div class=\"kt-inside-inner-col\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-tweaks\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/2699.png\" alt=\"⚙\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Tweaks</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p>Tweaks in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Add aria-label attribute to events navigation.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Changed views: <code>modules/meta/organizer</code>, <code>v2/components/content-title</code>, <code>v2/components/header</code>, <code>v2/day/nav</code>, <code>v2/day/top-bar/nav</code>, <code>v2/month/calendar-body/day/cell-title</code>, <code>v2/month/calendar-body/day/date</code>, <code>v2/month/top-bar/nav</code> </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Improve Day View content title to display contextual &#8220;Events for [Date]&#8221; format at the top of the view.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Improve heading hierarchy in month view by making date headings only when events are present.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Improve keyboard focus order in zoomed/mobile layouts to follow a more logical and predictable sequence, aligning with WCAG best practices.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Improve mini calendar accessibility by adding non-color indicators for past, current, and upcoming days.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column2553086_a64b83-bf\"><div class=\"kt-inside-inner-col\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-translations\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f5e3.png\" alt=\"🗣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Translations</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p>Updated language files and strings:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>3 new strings added</li>\n\n\n\n<li>11 updated</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 fuzzied</li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 obsoleted</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div></div>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-events-calendar-6-15-16/\">The Events Calendar 6.15.16</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23:\"Event Aggregator 2.7.13\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/event-aggregator-2-7-13/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xm